<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFFBFFDDA5F8F8CF1AB5FE89" blockId="11.[136,1452,1166,2093]" lastBlockId="12.[136,1452,158,365]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="13" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFBFFDAA5F8F8CF1F19F8F0" bold="true" box="[189,294,1814,1840]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFFBFFDAA463F8CF1FC0F8F0" authorityName="P. Peralta &amp; Thode" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Velloso" box="[294,511,1814,1840]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Glandularia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lobata">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFBFFDAA463F8CF1FC0F8F0" box="[294,511,1814,1840]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Glandularia lobata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has two varieties: 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFFBFFDAA795F8CE1B94F8F0" authority="(Moldenke) P. Peralta &amp; Thode (2010: 30)" authorityName="P. Peralta &amp; Thode" authorityPageNumber="30" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Moldenke" box="[720,1451,1814,1841]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Glandularia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="lobata" variety="glabrata">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFBFFDAA795F8CE1D05F8F0" box="[720,826,1814,1841]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">G. lobata</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFBFFDAA634F8CF1DEEF8F0" box="[881,977,1814,1840]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">glabrata</emphasis>
(Moldenke) P. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFFBFFDAA133F8CF1B94F8F0" author="Peralta, P. &amp; Thode, V." box="[1142,1451,1814,1840]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="32" refId="ref37323" refString="Peralta, P. &amp; Thode, V. (2010) Una nueva especie, un nuevo status y nuevas combinaciones en Glandularia (Verbenaceae) para el Sur de Brazil. Rodriguesia 61: S 29 - S 32. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / 2175 - 7860201061128" type="journal article" year="2010">Peralta &amp; Thode (2010: 30)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and the type-variety. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFFBFFDAA74BF8E31D14F895" author="O'Leary, N. &amp; Thode, V." box="[526,811,1850,1877]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="699 - 750" refId="ref36712" refString="O'Leary, N. &amp; Thode, V. (2016) The genus Glandularia (Verbenaceae) in Brazil. Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden 101: 699 - 750. https: // doi. org / 10.3417 / 2014008" type="journal article" year="2016">O’Leary &amp; Thode (2016)</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFFBFFDAA677F8E21A0BF894" authorityName="P. Peralta &amp; Thode" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Moldenke" box="[818,1076,1850,1877]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Glandularia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="lobata" variety="glabrata">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFBFFDAA677F8E21DA3F894" box="[818,924,1850,1877]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">G. lobata</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFBFFDAA691F8E31A0BF894" box="[980,1076,1850,1876]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">glabrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is different from the type-variety by the presence of strigose branches, trimerous inflorescences, and glandular trichomes absent in the bracts and calyx, while 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFFBFFDAA595F85A1FFDF85C" authority="var. lobata" box="[208,450,1922,1949]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Glandularia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="lobata" variety="lobata">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFBFFDAA595F85A1F01F85C" box="[208,318,1922,1949]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">G. lobata</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFBFFDAA43FF85B1FFDF85C" box="[378,450,1922,1948]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">lobata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presents hirsute branches, tetramerous inflorescences, and glandular trichomes present in bracts and calyx. However, the analysis of several collections of 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFFBFFDAA6C7F87E1DD2F800" authorityName="P. Peralta &amp; Thode" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Velloso" box="[898,1005,1958,1985]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Glandularia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lobata">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFBFFDAA6C7F87E1DD2F800" box="[898,1005,1958,1985]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">G. lobata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFFBFFDAA6B9F87F1AD5F800" author="Cardoso, P. H. &amp; Cabral, A. &amp; Santos-Silva, F. &amp; Salimena, F. R. G." box="[1020,1258,1958,1984]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="1 - 15" refId="ref33573" refString="Cardoso, P. H., Cabral, A., Santos-Silva, F. &amp; Salimena, F. R. G. (2019 a) Verbenaceae no Parque Estadual da Serra do Papagaio, Minas Gerais, Brasil. Rodriguesia 70: 1 - 15. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / 2175 - 7860201970056" type="journal article" year="2019">
Cardoso 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFBFFDAA126F87E1AA3F800" box="[1123,1180,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al.</emphasis>
2019a
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFFBFFDAA1B3F87F1B02F800" author="Cardoso, P. H. &amp; Santos-Silva, F. &amp; Menini-Neto, L. &amp; Salimena, F. R. G." box="[1270,1341,1958,1984]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref34122" refString="Cardoso, P. H., Santos-Silva, F., Menini-Neto, L. Salimena, F. R. G. (2019 e) Verbenaceae no Parque Nacional do Caparao, Serra da Mantiqueira, Brasil. Hoehnea 46: 1 - 12. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / 2236 - 8906 - 65 / 2019" type="journal article" year="2019">2019e</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFFBFFDAA00CF87F1F37F824" author="Santiago, A. O. &amp; Cardoso, P. H. &amp; Salimena, F. R. G. &amp; Trovo, M." pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="1 - 9" refId="ref38676" refString="Santiago, A. O., Cardoso, P. H., Salimena, F. R. G. &amp; Trovo, M. (2020) Verbenaceae no Parque Nacional do Itatiaia, Brasil. Rodriguesia 71: 1 - 9. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / 2175 - 7860202071066" type="journal article" year="2020">
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFFBFFDAA00CF87F1B94F800" box="[1353,1451,1958,1984]" country="Philippines" name="Santiago" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Santiago</collectingRegion>
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFBFFDAA5CDF8121EFBF824" box="[136,196,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
) has not allowed us to follow this delimitation. We observed a wide variation in the indument of the branches (from glabrescent to strigose or densely hirsute), and the arrangement of the inflorescences (both trimerous or tetramerous) is not always associated to the indument patterns established in the circumscription of the varieties. Similarly, the presence or absence of glandular trichomes in the bracts and calyx are not also related to the other characteristics used for delimitation of the infraspecific taxa. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFFCFFDDA67CFF1B1A6AFF1D" author="O'Leary, N. &amp; Thode, V." box="[825,1109,194,221]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="699 - 750" refId="ref36712" refString="O'Leary, N. &amp; Thode, V. (2016) The genus Glandularia (Verbenaceae) in Brazil. Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden 101: 699 - 750. https: // doi. org / 10.3417 / 2014008" type="journal article" year="2016">O’Leary &amp; Thode (2016)</bibRefCitation>
recorded the occurrence of 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFFCFFDDA0D5FF1A1F70FEC0" authority="var. lobata" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Glandularia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="lobata" variety="lobata">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFCFFDDA0D5FF1A1EEFFEC0" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">G. lobata</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFCFFDDA442FF3F1F70FEC0" box="[263,335,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">lobata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFFCFFDDA4E0FF3F1C40FEC1" box="[421,639,230,257]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Espírito Santo state</collectingRegion>
(
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFCFFDDA7CAFF3E1D34FEC0" box="[655,779,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Irwin 2783</emphasis>
(NY)), but this specimen presented neither hirsute branches nor inflorescences arranged in a tetramerous disposition, showing a nitid confusion about the infraspecific taxa of 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFFCFFDDA0D5FED21EEFFE88" authorityName="P. Peralta &amp; Thode" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Velloso" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Glandularia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lobata">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFCFFDDA0D5FED21EEFFE88" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">G. lobata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Further studies are needed to understand the delimitation of these infraspecific taxa.
</paragraph>
